SWIMMING pools which were closed ­because the water was not deemed acceptable will not reopen until October 6. Closure-hit pools set to remain shut SWIMMING pools which were closed ­because the water was not deemed acceptable will not reopen until October 6.Chemical readings taken during routine water quality tests at Eastwood Park Leisure pools showed there were technical issues.East Renfrewshire Council said the problem posed no threat to public health.Sand filters, which are used to remove &shy;debris from pool water are being replaced, and improvements are being made to the plumbing of the pools. 